README for guile-gobject
========================

Abstract:
---------

guile-gobject is a Guile wrapper collection for the GNOME
libraries. It ships with an wrapper engine that allows semi-automatic
wrapping of GObject-based C APIs (GNOME2, but also other non-GNOME
projects).

Copyright:
----------
Distribution of library and components is under the GPL as listed in the
file COPYING.

Contact info:
-------------
  Mailing List: mailto: guile-gtk-general@gnu.org
  Homepage:     http://www.gnu.org/software/guile-gtk
  Download:     http://www.gnu.org/software/guile-gtk/download

Build-Dependencies:
--------------------

* Guile 1.6.4 or newer.
* G-Wrap TNG, available from 
  http://www.nongnu.org/g-wrap/TheNextGeneration.html

Installation Quickstart:
------------------------

Install using the standard autotools incantation:
  ./configure && make && make install.

Build from CVS or Arch using ./autogen.sh && make.

You can run without installing, just run './dev-environ guile'.

The guile-gobject Developers, 29 Mar 2004
